                             -     *  the given InputStream.                           
                             -     *                                                   
                             -     * <p>Your input stream MUST either                  
                             support mark/reset, or                                    
                             -     *  be wrapped as a {@link                           
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             -     *  Note that using an {@link                        
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             -     *  than using a {@link File}.</p>                   
                             -     *                                                   
                             -     * <p>Note that in order to properly                 
                             release resources the                                     
                             -     *  Workbook should be closed after                  
                             use. Note also that loading                               
                             -     *  from an InputStream requires                     
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             -     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                    
                             #create(File)} where possible.                            
                             +    private static Workbook wp(FileMagic                 
                             magic, ProviderMethod method) throws                      
                             IOException {                                             
                             +        IOException lastException =                      
                             null;                                                     
                             +        RuntimeException                                 
                             lastRuntimeException = null;                              
                             +        for (WorkbookProvider prov :                     
                             provider) {                                               
                             +            boolean accepted;                            
                             +            try {                                        
                             +                accepted =                               
                             prov.accepts(magic);                                      
                             +            } catch (IOException e) {                    
                             +                // error during magic                    
                             check, record and try next provider                       
                             +                lastException = e;                       
                             +                continue;                                
                             +            } catch (RuntimeException e)                 
                             {                                                         
                             +                lastRuntimeException =                   
                             e;                                                        
                             +                continue;                                
                             +            }                                            
                             +            if (!accepted) {                             
                             +                // provider does not                     
                             handle this magic, continue                               
                             +                continue;                                
                             +            }                                            
                             +            // On provider match,                        
                             propagate parsing exceptions from                         
                             create()                                                  
                             +            return method.create(prov);                  
                             +        }                                                
                             +        // No provider matched                           
                             successfully, rethrow first encountered                   
                             exception if any                                          
                             +        if (lastException != null) {                     
                             +            throw lastException;                         
                             +        }                                                
                             +        if (lastRuntimeException !=                      
                             null) {                                                   
                             +            throw lastRuntimeException;                  
                             +        }                                                
                             +        throw new                                        
                             IllegalArgumentException("Unsupported                     
                             workbook magic: " + magic);                               
                             +    }                                                    
                                   *                                                   
                                   *  @param inp The {@link                            
                             InputStream} to read data from.                           
                                   *

                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                                                                                       
                             The issue report consists of the raw                      
                             execution log from running the                            
                             POIHSSFFuzzer harness against the Apache                  
                             POI HSSF codebase under Jazzer/libFuzzer.                 
                             It shows environment setup, fuzzer                        
                             invocation parameters, the loading and                    
                             instrumentation of numerous classes and                   
                             sanitizers, and the absence of any crash                  
                             or error beyond deprecation and                           
                             bootstrap-classpath warnings.                             
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             - **What the issue is:**                                  
                               The provided issue is a console log                     
                             from an interactive fuzzing session. It                   
                             documents:                                                
                                Setting environment variables                         
                             (RUN_FUZZER_MODE, FUZZING_ENGINE,                         
                             SKIP_SEED_CORPUS)                                         
                                Invocation of the fuzzer executable                   
                             `/out/POIHSSFFuzzer` with flags                           
                             `-rss_limit_mb=2560`, `-timeout=25`,                      
                             `-runs=100`, and a single input                           
                             `/testcase`.                                              
                                Java VM startup warnings about                        
                             deprecated JNI options and classpath                      
                             sharing restrictions.                                     
                                Jazzer initialization: loading                        
                             tracing and sanitizer hooks for various                   
                             vulnerability classes (e.g., SQL                          
                             injection, file path traversal,                           
                             deserialization).                                         
                                Instrumentation of hundreds of                        
                             classes from Apache POI (HSSF, HPSF,                      
                             OOXML, commons-io, log4j integration),                    
                             with timing and code-size overhead                        
                             metrics.                                                  
                                libFuzzer engine information (seed,                   
                             module count, coverage counters, entropy                  
                             schedule).                                                
                                No crash, exception, or sanitizer                     
                             violation is reported; the run appears to                 
                             complete its 100 iterations without                       
                             detecting a failure.                                      
                                                                                       
                             - **Vulnerability type:**                                 
                               No explicit vulnerability or crash is                   
                             surfaced in the log. Although the                         
                             instrumentation includes hooks for common                 
                             vulnerability categories (e.g., SQL                       
                             injection, SSRF, command injection), the                  
                             fuzzer did not report any triggered                       
                             sanitizer or hook violation.                              
                                                                                       
                             - **Important observations and                            
                             findings:**                                               
                               1. The harness successfully instruments                 
                             a very large set of classes, indicating                   
                             broad coverage of the POI codebase and                    
                             its dependencies (commons-io, log4j).                     
                               2. Jazzers sanitizer hooks for various                 
                             vulnerability types are loaded but none                   
                             are invoked to signal a finding.                          
                               3. The run completed 100 executions of                  
                             the single testcase input without timeout                 
                             or memory-limit breaches.                                 
                               4. The harness disables seed corpus                     
                             processing (`SKIP_SEED_CORPUS=1`) and                     
                             uses an interactive mode, suggesting a                    
                             manual or debugging session rather than                   
                             automated fuzz regression.                                
                                                                                       
                             - **Code areas to investigate for a                       
                             holistic view:**                                          
                                The fuzzer entry point class                          
                             `org.apache.poi.POIHSSFFuzzer`: how it                    
                             constructs and feeds inputs to the HSSF                   
                             parsing routines.                                         
                                The initialization and invocation of                  
                             Jazzers sanitizer hooks within                           
                             `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.runtime`.                   
                                Apache POI modules under test:                        
                             especially the HSSF record parsers                        
                             (`org.apache.poi.hssf.record.*`) and                      
                             high-level workbook I/O                                   
                             (`org.apache.poi.hssf.usermodel.HSSFWorkb                 
                             ook`).                                                    
                                The harness shell script (`run_fuzzer                 
                             POIHSSFFuzzer ...`) for correct flag                      
                             passing and timeout semantics.                            
                                Interaction with logging frameworks                   
                             (log4j) and commons-io streams, as these                  
                             were instrumented with custom hooks                      
                             only and may affect coverage or                          
                             performance.                                              
                                                                                       
                             No root-cause or bug has been identified                  
                             from this log; rather, it provides the                    
                             baseline instrumentation and execution                    
                             context for further fuzzing efforts.                      
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log

                             290:    public static String                              
                             getWorkbookDirEntryName(DirectoryNode                     
                             directory) {                                              
                             291:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(WORKBO                 
                             OK)) {                                                    
                             292:            return WORKBOOK;                          
                             293:        }                                             
                             294:                                                      
                             295:        // check for an encrypted                     
                             .xlsx file - they get OLE2 wrapped                        
                             296:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(Decryp                 
                             tor.DEFAULT_POIFS_ENTRY)) {                               
                             297:            throw new

                             298:                    "It must be                       
                             decrypted before use by XSSF, it cannot                   
                             be used by HSSF");

                             301:        // check case-sensitive for                   
                             previous version of file format                           
                             302:        if

                             Y_NAME)) {                                                
                             303:            throw new

                             304:                    + "POI only                       
                             supports BIFF8 format (from Excel

                             305:        }                                             
                             306:                                                      
                             307:        //check for                                   
                             non-case-sensitive book (e.g. crystal)                    
                             after ruling out case-sensitive                           
                             308:        // OldExcelFormatException                    
                             309:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(BOOK))                 
                             {                                                         
                             310:            return BOOK;                              
                             311:        }                                             
                             312:                                                      
                             313:        // throw more useful                          
                             exceptions for known wrong                                
                             file-extensions                                           
                             314:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive("WordD                 
                             ocument")) {                                              
                             315:            throw new                                 
                             IllegalArgumentException("The document is                 
                             really a DOC file");                                      
                             316:        }                                             
                             317:                                                      
                             318:        throw new

                             POIFSFileSystem does not contain a BIFF8

                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/poifs/fi                 
                             lesystem/POIFSFileSystem.java:50-150                      
                             ```                                                       
                             50:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.poifs.storage.HeaderBlock;                 
                             51:import org.apache.poi.util.IOUtils;                    
                             52:import org.apache.poi.util.Internal;                   
                             53:                                                       
                             54:/**                                                    
                             55: * <p>This is the main class of the                    
                             POIFS system; it manages the entire                       
                             56: * life cycle of the filesystem.</p>                   
                             57: * <p>This is the new NIO version,                     
                             which uses less memory</p>                                
                             58: */                                                    
                             59:                                                       
                             60:public class POIFSFileSystem extends                   
                             BlockStore                                                
                             61:        implements POIFSViewable,                      
                             Closeable {                                               
                             62:    //arbitrarily selected; may need                   
                             to increase                                               
                             63:    private static final int                           
                             DEFAULT_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH = 100_000;                      
                             64:    private static int                                 
                             MAX_RECORD_LENGTH =                                       
                             DEFAULT_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;                                
                             65:                                                       
                             66:    private static final int                           
                             MAX_ALLOCATION_SIZE = 250_000_000;                        
                             67:                                                       
                             68:    private static final Logger LOG =                  
                             PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIFSFileSystem.c                 
                             lass);                                                    
                             69:                                                       
                             70:    /**                                                
                             71:     * Maximum number size (in blocks)                 
                             of the allocation table as supported by                   
                             72:     * POI.                                            
                             73:     * <p>                                             
                             74:     * This constant has been chosen                   
                             to help POI identify corrupted data in                    
                             the                                                       
                             75:     * header block (rather than crash                 
                             immediately with {@link OutOfMemoryError}                 
                             76:     * ). It's not clear if the                        
                             compound document format actually                         
                             specifies any                                             
                             77:     * upper limits. For files with                    
                             512 byte blocks, having an allocation                     
                             table                                                     
                             78:     * of 65,335 blocks would                          
                             correspond to a total file size of 4GB.                   
                             Needless                                                  
                             79:     * to say, POI probably cannot                     
                             handle files anywhere near that size.                     
                             80:     */                                                
                             81:    private static final int                           
                             MAX_BLOCK_COUNT = 65535;                                  
                             82:                                                       
                             83:    private POIFSMiniStore                             
                             _mini_store;                                              
                             84:    private PropertyTable                              
                             _property_table;                                          
                             85:    private final List<BATBlock>                       
                             _xbat_blocks;                                             
                             86:    private final List<BATBlock>                       
                             _bat_blocks;                                              
                             87:    private HeaderBlock _header;                       
                             88:    private DirectoryNode _root;                       
                             89:                                                       
                             90:    protected DataSource _data;                        
                             91:                                                       
                             92:    /**                                                
                             93:     * What big block size the file                    
                             uses. Most files                                          
                             94:     * use 512 bytes, but a few use                    
                             4096                                                      
                             95:     */                                                
                             96:    private POIFSBigBlockSize                          
                             bigBlockSize =                                            
                             97:                                                       
                             POIFSConstants.SMALLER_BIG_BLOCK_SIZE_DET                 
                             AILS;                                                     
                             98:                                                       
                             99:    /**                                                
                             100:     * @param length the max record                   
                             length allowed for POIFSFileSystem                        
                             101:     */                                               
                             102:    public static void                                
                             setMaxRecordLength(int length) {                          
                             103:        MAX_RECORD_LENGTH = length;                   
                             104:    }                                                 
                             105:                                                      
                             106:    /**                                               
                             107:     * @return the max record length                  
                             allowed for POIFSFileSystem                               
                             108:     */                                               
                             109:    public static int                                 
                             getMaxRecordLength() {                                    
                             110:        return MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;                     
                             111:    }                                                 
                             112:                                                      
                             113:    private POIFSFileSystem(boolean                   
                             newFS) {                                                  
                             114:        _header = new                                 
                             HeaderBlock(bigBlockSize);                                
                             115:        _property_table = new                         
                             PropertyTable(_header);                                   
                             116:        _mini_store = new                             
                             POIFSMiniStore(this,                                      
                             _property_table.getRoot(), new                            
                             ArrayList<>(), _header);                                  
                             117:        _xbat_blocks = new                            
                             ArrayList<>();                                            
                             118:        _bat_blocks = new                             
                             ArrayList<>();                                            
                             119:        _root = null;                                 
                             120:                                                      
                             121:        if (newFS) {                                  
                             122:            createNewDataSource();                    
                             123:        }                                             
                             124:    }                                                 
                             125:                                                      
                             126:    protected void                                    
                             createNewDataSource() {                                   
                             127:        // Data needs to initially                    
                             hold just the header block,                               
                             128:        //  a single bat block, and                   
                             an empty properties section                               
                             129:        long blockSize =                              
                             Math.multiplyExact(bigBlockSize.getBigBlo                 
                             ckSize(), 3L);                                            
                             130:        _data = new                                   
                             ByteArrayBackedDataSource(IOUtils.safelyA                 
                             llocate(blockSize, MAX_RECORD_LENGTH));                   
                             131:    }                                                 
                             132:                                                      
                             133:    /**                                               
                             134:     * Constructor, intended for                      
                             writing                                                   
                             135:     */                                               
                             136:    public POIFSFileSystem() {                        
                             137:        this(true);                                   
                             138:                                                      
                             139:        // Reserve block 0 for the                    
                             start of the Properties Table                             
                             140:        // Create a single empty BAT,                 
                             at pop that at offset 1                                   
                             141:        _header.setBATCount(1);                       
                             142:        _header.setBATArray(new                       
                             int[]{1});                                                
                             143:        BATBlock bb =                                 
                             BATBlock.createEmptyBATBlock(bigBlockSize                 
                             , false);                                                 
                             144:        bb.setOurBlockIndex(1);                       
                             145:        _bat_blocks.add(bb);                          
                             146:                                                      
                             147:        setNextBlock(0,                               
                             POIFSConstants.END_OF_CHAIN);                             
                             148:        setNextBlock(1,                               
                             POIFSConstants.FAT_SECTOR_BLOCK);                         
                             149:                                                      
                             150:                                                      
                             _property_table.setStartBlock(0);                         
                             ```

                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/poifs/fi                 
                             lesystem/POIFSFileSystem.java:160-200                     
                             ```                                                       
                             160:     *                                                
                             161:     * @param file the File from                      
                             which to read the data                                    
                             162:     * @throws IOException on errors                  
                             reading, or on invalid data                               
                             163:     */                                               
                             164:    public POIFSFileSystem(File file)                 
                             165:            throws IOException {                      
                             166:        this(file, true);                             
                             167:    }                                                 
                             168:                                                      
                             169:    /**                                               
                             170:     * <p>Creates a POIFSFileSystem                   
                             from a {@code File}. This uses less                       
                             memory than                                               
                             171:     * creating from an {@code                        
                             InputStream}.</p>                                         
                             172:     *                                                
                             173:     * <p>Note that with this                         
                             constructor, you will need to call {@link                 
                             #close()}                                                 
                             174:     * when you're done to have the                   
                             underlying file closed, as the file is                    
                             175:     * kept open during normal                        
                             operation to read the data out.</p>                       
                             176:     *                                                
                             177:     * @param file     the File from                  
                             which to read or read/write the data                      
                             178:     * @param readOnly whether the                    
                             POIFileSystem will only be used in                        
                             read-only mode                                            
                             179:     * @throws IOException on errors                  
                             reading, or on invalid data                               
                             180:     */                                               
                             181:    public POIFSFileSystem(File file,                 
                             boolean readOnly)                                         
                             182:            throws IOException {                      
                             183:        this(null, file, readOnly,                    
                             true, true);                                              
                             184:    }                                                 
                             185:                                                      
                             186:    /**                                               
                             187:     * <p>Creates a POIFSFileSystem                   
                             from an open {@code FileChannel}. This                    
                             uses                                                      
                             188:     * less memory than creating from                 
                             an {@code InputStream}. The stream will                   
                             189:     * be used in read-only mode.</p>                 
                             190:     *                                                
                             191:     * <p>Note that with this                         
                             constructor, you will need to call {@link                 
                             #close()}                                                 
                             192:     * when you're done to have the                   
                             underlying Channel closed, as the channel                 
                             is                                                        
                             193:     * kept open during normal                        
                             operation to read the data out. For                       
                             legacy reasons,                                           
                             194:     * the channel is not closed if                   
                             there is an error creating the                            
                             POIFSFileSystem.</p>                                      
                             195:     *                                                
                             196:     * @param channel the FileChannel                 
                             from which to read the data                               
                             197:     * @throws IOException on errors                  
                             reading, or on invalid data                               
                             198:     * @see                                           
                             #POIFSFileSystem(FileChannel, boolean,                    
                             boolean) this constructor gives more                      
                             control over whether to                                   
                             199:     * close the provided channel                     
                             200:     */                                               
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>

                             289:                                                      
                             290:    public static String

                             297:            throw new

                             spreadsheet seems to be an Encrypted                      
                             .xlsx file. " +                                           
                             298:                    "It must be                       
                             decrypted before use by XSSF, it cannot                   
                             be used by HSSF");                                        
                             299:        }                                             
                             300:                                                      
                             301:        // check case-sensitive for                   
                             previous version of file format                           
                             302:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntry(OLD_WORKBOOK_DIR_ENTR                 
                             Y_NAME)) {                                                
                             303:            throw new                                 
                             OldExcelFormatException("The supplied                     
                             spreadsheet seems to be Excel 5.0/7.0                     
                             (BIFF5) format. "                                         
                             304:                    + "POI only                       
                             supports BIFF8 format (from Excel                         
                             versions 97/2000/XP/2003)");                              
                             305:        }                                             
                             306:                                                      
                             307:        //check for                                   
                             non-case-sensitive book (e.g. crystal)                    
                             after ruling out case-sensitive                           
                             308:        // OldExcelFormatException                    
                             309:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(BOOK))                 
                             {                                                         
                             310:            return BOOK;                              
                             311:        }                                             
                             312:                                                      
                             313:        // throw more useful                          
                             exceptions for known wrong                                
                             file-extensions                                           
                             314:        if                                            
                             (directory.hasEntryCaseInsensitive("WordD                 
                             ocument")) {                                              
                             315:            throw new                                 
                             IllegalArgumentException("The document is                 
                             really a DOC file");                                      
                             316:        }                                             
                             317:                                                      
                             318:        throw new                                     
                             IllegalArgumentException("The supplied                    
                             POIFSFileSystem does not contain a BIFF8                  
                             'Workbook' entry. "                                       
                             319:                + "Is it really an                    
                             excel file? Had: " +                                      
                             directory.getEntryNames());                               
                             320:    }                                                 
                             321:                                                      
                             322:    /**                                               
                             323:     * given a POI POIFSFileSystem                    
                             object, and a specific directory                          
                             324:     * within it, read in its                         
                             Workbook and populate the high and                        
                             325:     * low level models.  If you're                   
                             reading in a workbook...start here.                       
                             326:     *                                                
                             327:     * @param directory     the POI                   
                             filesystem directory to process from                      
                             328:     * @param fs            the POI                   
                             filesystem that contains the Workbook                     
                             stream.                                                   
                             329:     * @param preserveNodes whether                   
                             to preserve other nodes, such as                          
                             330:     *                      macros.                   
                             This takes more memory, so only say yes                   
                             if you                                                    
                             331:     *                      need to.                  
                             If set, will store all of the                             
                             POIFSFileSystem                                           
                             332:     *                      in memory                 
                             333:     * @throws IOException if the                     
                             stream cannot be read                                     
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>

                             38:/**                                                    
                             39: * Factory for creating the                            
                             appropriate kind of Workbook                              
                             40: *  (be it {@link HSSFWorkbook} or                     
                             XSSFWorkbook),                                            
                             41: *  by auto-detecting from the                         
                             supplied input.

                             43:public final class WorkbookFactory {                   
                             44:                                                       
                             45:    private static class Singleton {                   
                             46:        private static final                           
                             WorkbookFactory INSTANCE = new                            
                             WorkbookFactory();                                        
                             47:    }                                                  
                             48:                                                       
                             49:    private interface ProviderMethod {                 
                             50:        Workbook                                       
                             create(WorkbookProvider prov) throws                      
                             IOException;                                              
                             51:    }                                                  
                             52:                                                       
                             53:    private final                                      
                             List<WorkbookProvider> provider = new                     
                             ArrayList<>();                                            
                             54:                                                       
                             55:    private WorkbookFactory() {                        
                             56:        ClassLoader cl =                               
                             WorkbookFactory.class.getClassLoader();                   
                             57:                                                       
                             ServiceLoader.load(WorkbookProvider.class                 
                             , cl).forEach(provider::add);                             
                             58:    }                                                  
                             59:                                                       
                             60:                                                       
                             61:    /**                                                
                             62:     * Create a new empty Workbook,                    
                             either XSSF or HSSF depending                             
                             63:     * on the parameter                                
                             64:     *                                                 
                             65:     * @param xssf If an XSSFWorkbook                  
                             or a HSSFWorkbook should be created                       
                             66:     *                                                 
                             67:     * @return The created workbook                    
                             68:     *                                                 
                             69:     * @throws IOException if an error                 
                             occurs while creating the objects                         
                             70:     * @throws IllegalStateException a                 
                             number of other runtime exceptions can be                 
                             thrown, especially if there are problems                  
                             with the                                                  
                             71:     * input format                                    
                             72:     */                                                
                             73:    public static Workbook                             
                             create(boolean xssf) throws IOException {                 
                             74:        return wp(xssf ?                               
                             FileMagic.OOXML : FileMagic.OLE2,                         
                             WorkbookProvider::create);                                
                             75:    }                                                  
                             76:                                                       
                             77:    /**

                             properly release resources the                            
                             81:     * Workbook should be closed after                 
                             use.

                             88:     * @throws IllegalStateException a

                             thrown, especially if there are problems                  
                             with the                                                  
                             89:     * input format                                    
                             90:     */                                                
                             91:    public static Workbook                             
                             create(POIFSFileSystem fs) throws                         
                             IOException {                                             
                             92:        return create(fs, null);                       
                             93:    }                                                  
                             94:                                                       
                             95:    /**                                                
                             96:     * Creates a Workbook from the

                             97:     *  be password protected.                         
                             98:     *

                             properly release resources the                            
                             100:     * Workbook should be closed                      
                             after use.

                             from

                             that should be used or null if no                         
                             password is necessary.                                    
                             104:     *                                                
                             105:     *  @return The created Workbook                  
                             106:     *                                                
                             107:     *  @throws IOException if an                     
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             108:     *  @throws IllegalStateException                 
                             a number of runtime exceptions can be                     
                             thrown, especially if there are problems                  
                             with the                                                  
                             109:     *  input format                                  
                             110:     */                                               
                             111:    private static Workbook                           
                             create(final POIFSFileSystem fs, String                   
                             password) throws IOException {                            
                             112:        return create(fs.getRoot(),                   
                             password);                                                
                             113:    }                                                 
                             114:                                                      
                             115:

                             120:     * Workbook should be closed                      
                             after use.                                                
                             121:     *

                             DirectoryNode} to start reading the                       
                             document from                                             
                             123:     *                                                
                             124:     * @return The created Workbook                   
                             125:     *                                                
                             126:     * @throws IOException if an

                             127:     * @throws IllegalStateException                  
                             a number of other exceptions can be

                             132:    }

                             that should be used or null if no                         
                             password is necessary.                                    
                             144:     *                                                
                             145:     * @return The created Workbook                   
                             146:     *                                                
                             147:     * @throws IOException if an                      
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             148:     * @throws IllegalStateException                  
                             a number of runtime exceptions can be                     
                             thrown, especially if there are problems                  
                             with the                                                  
                             149:     * input format                                   
                             150:     */                                               
                             ```
