                             ```                                                       
                             150:     */                                               
                             151:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(final DirectoryNode root, String                   
                             password) throws IOException {                            
                             152:        // Encrypted OOXML files go                   
                             inside OLE2 containers, is this one?                      
                             153:        if                                            
                             (root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(DEFAULT_POI                 
                             FS_ENTRY) ||                                              
                             root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(OOXML_PACKAG                 
                             E)) {                                                     
                             154:            return                                    
                             wp(FileMagic.OOXML, w -> w.create(root,                   
                             password));                                               
                             155:        } else {                                      
                             156:            return wp(FileMagic.OLE2,                 
                             w ->  w.create(root, password));                          
                             157:        }                                             
                             158:    }                                                 
                             159:                                                      
                             160:    /**                                               
                             161:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             162:     *  the given InputStream.                        
                             163:     *                                                
                             164:     * <p>Your input stream MUST                      
                             either support mark/reset, or                             
                             165:     *  be wrapped as a {@link                        
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             166:     *  Note that using an {@link                     
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             167:     *  than using a {@link                           
                             File}.</p>                                                
                             168:     *                                                
                             169:     * <p>Note that in order to                       
                             properly release resources the                            
                             170:     *  Workbook should be closed                     
                             after use. Note also that loading                         
                             171:     *  from an InputStream requires                  
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             172:     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                 
                             #create(File)} where possible.                            
                             173:     *                                                
                             174:     *  @param inp The {@link                         
                             InputStream} to read data from.                           
                             175:     *                                                
                             176:     *  @return The created Workbook                  
                             177:     *                                                
                             178:     *  @throws IOException if an                     
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             179:     *  @throws                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException If the                         
                             Workbook given is password protected                      
                             180:     *  @throws EmptyFileException If                 
                             the given data is empty                                   
                             181:     *  @throws IllegalStateException                 
                             a number of other runtime exceptions can                  
                             be thrown, especially if there are                        
                             problems with the                                         
                             182:     *  input format                                  
                             183:     */                                               
                             184:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(InputStream inp) throws                            
                             IOException, EncryptedDocumentException {                 
                             185:        return create(inp, null);                     
                             186:    }                                                 
                             187:                                                      
                             188:    /**                                               
                             189:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             190:     *  the given InputStream, which                  
                             may be password protected.                                
                             191:     *                                                
                             192:     * <p>Your input stream MUST                      
                             either support mark/reset, or                             
                             193:     *  be wrapped as a {@link                        
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             194:     *  Note that using an {@link                     
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             195:     *  than using a {@link                           
                             File}.</p>                                                
                             196:     *                                                
                             197:     * <p>Note that in order to                       
                             properly release resources the                            
                             198:     *  Workbook should be closed                     
                             after use. Note also that loading                         
                             199:     *  from an InputStream requires                  
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             200:     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                 
                             #create(File)} where possible.</p>                        
                             201:     *                                                
                             202:     *  @param inp The {@link                         
                             InputStream} to read data from.                           
                             203:     *  @param password The password                  
                             that should be used or null if no                         
                             password is necessary.                                    
                             204:     *                                                
                             205:     *  @return The created Workbook                  
                             206:     *                                                
                             207:     *  @throws IOException if an                     
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             208:     *  @throws                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException If the wrong                   
                             password is given for a protected file                    
                             209:     *  @throws EmptyFileException If                 
                             the given data is empty                                   
                             210:     *  @throws IllegalStateException                 
                             a number of other runtime exceptions can                  
                             be thrown, especially if there are                        
                             problems with the                                         
                             211:     *  input format                                  
                             212:     */                                               
                             213:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(InputStream inp, String password)                  
                             throws IOException,                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException {                              
                             214:        InputStream is =                              
                             FileMagic.prepareToCheckMagic(inp);                       
                             215:        byte[] emptyFileCheck = new                   
                             byte[1];                                                  
                             216:                                                      
                             is.mark(emptyFileCheck.length);                           
                             217:        if (is.read(emptyFileCheck) <                 
                             emptyFileCheck.length) {                                  
                             218:            throw new                                 
                             EmptyFileException();                                     
                             219:        }                                             
                             220:        is.reset();                                   
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>                                                   
                             </code_snippets>                                          
                                                                                       
                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Identify exception-suppression in                      
                             WorkbookFactory:                                          
                                - The core of WorkbookFactorys                        
                             `wp(FileMagic, ProviderMethod)` method                    
                             loops through all registered                              
                             `WorkbookProvider`s (HSSF, XSSF, etc.).                   
                                - For each provider, it does something                 
                             like:                                                     
                                    try { if (prov.accepts(magic))                     
                             return method.create(prov); }                             
                                    catch(IOException|RuntimeException                 
                             e) { remember exception; continue; }                      
                                - If none succeeds, it ultimately                      
                             wraps/throws only the _last_ caught                       
                             exception or a generic                                    
                             IllegalArgumentException without exposing                 
                             the original parse error.                                 
                                - As a result, when a malformed BIFF                   
                             stream triggers a `RecordFormatException`                 
                             or other parsing exception in                             
                             HSSFWorkbook, WorkbookFactory swallows it                 
                             (logging nothing), continues to next                      
                             provider, then hides the original error.                  
                             2. Symptoms & root cause:                                 
                                - The fuzzer harness invokes                           
                             `WorkbookFactory.create(...)` (or                         
                             HSSFWorkbookFactory directly), but any                    
                             low-level parsing error is caught and                     
                             suppressed by the factory, so the harness                 
                             never sees a crash or sanitizer                           
                             violation. Instead, it quietly returns                    
                             null or throws a generic exception that                   
                             the harness itself catches and ignores.                   
                             3. Fix approach:                                          
                                A. Amend WorkbookFactory to propagate                  
                             the _first_ parsing exception                             
                             unconditionally when the providers                       
                             `accepts()` already matched the file                      
                             magic:                                                    
                                   - Change the exception handling in                  
                             `wp()` so that if a providers                            
                             `accepts()` returns true and its                          
                             `create()` method throws any                              
                             `IOException` or `RuntimeException`                       
                             (e.g., RecordFormatException), that                       
                             exception is immediately re-thrown and                    
                             not caught/suppressed.                                    
                                   - Only if a providers `accepts()`                  
                             is false or a provider fails to accept                    
                             should the loop move on without                           
                             propagating exception.                                    
                                B. Preserve existing logic for                         
                             non-matching providers:                                   
                                   - Retain the fallback mechanism: if                 
                             the file magic doesnt match HSSF, or if                  
                             HSSFs accept check is false, exceptions                  
                             should still be caught/suppressed until a                 
                             matching provider is found.                               
                                C. Ensure no breaking changes:                         
                                   - Do not modify the public                          
                             signature of WorkbookFactory.                             
                                   - Do not remove the fallback to                     
                             XSSF or other providers; only change                      
                             exception handling in the matched case.                   
                                   - Do not alter any harness or                       
                             fuzzing logic.                                            
                             4. Implementation steps:                                  
                                1. Open                                                
                             `poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/ss/user                 
                             model/WorkbookFactory.java` and locate                    
                             the private `wp(FileMagic magic,                          
                             ProviderMethod method)` method (around                    
                             lines 150220).                                           
                                2. Within the loop over `provider`                     
                             list:                                                     
                                     - Replace:                                        
                                        ```                                            
                                        try {                                          
                                          if (prov.accepts(magic)) {                   
                                            return                                     
                             method.create(prov);                                      
                                          }                                            
                                        }                                              
                             catch(IOException|RuntimeException e) {                   
                                          lastException = e;                           
                                          continue;                                    
                                        }                                              
                                        ```                                            
                                       with:                                           
                                        ```                                            
                                        if (prov.accepts(magic)) {                     
                                          // On a provider match, do                   
                             not suppress errors.                                      
                                          return method.create(prov);                  
                                        }                                              
                                        ```                                            
                                     - Move the `try-catch` outside                    
                             the `accepts()` check, so that:                           
                                        - We only catch exceptions                     
                             when `accepts()` is false, thereby                        
                             preserving fallback behavior.                             
                                        - Or, better, wrap only the                    
                             `prov.accepts(magic)` check in a                          
                             try-catch that ignores exceptions thrown                  
                             from the check (unlikely), but let                        
                             `create()` errors propagate.                              
                                3. After the loop, keep the existing                   
                             logic that throws `lastException` or a                    
                             new `IllegalStateException` if no                         
                             provider accepted.                                        
                             5. Rationale:                                             
                                - By re-throwing parsing exceptions                    
                             immediately for the matching provider,                    
                             the fuzzer will see genuine parsing                       
                             errors (e.g., RecordFormatException,                      
                             EOFException) as crashes, which they can                  
                             then report and triangulate.                              
                                - This fix does not alter any API                      
                             signatures or functionality for                           
                             production code: in normal use, invalid                   
                             files already generate exceptions.                        
                                - It only tightens exception handling                  
                             in the factorys fallback loop, ensuring                  
                             that matched providers errors are not                    
                             hidden.                                                   
                             6. Side effects and mitigation:                           
                                - In rare cases, an HSSF provider may                  
                             throw a recoverable parsing exception                     
                             that downstream code previously ignored                   
                             and handled. Those flows now will                         
                             propagate an exception instead of falling                 
                             back to XSSF. But this aligns with                        
                             expected behavior: if OLE2 file magic is                  
                             detected, only HSSF should be used.                       
                                - Existing tests for                                   
                             `WorkbookFactory.create()` should be                      
                             reviewed: if any test expected fallback                   
                             to XSSF on HSSF parse failure, it must be                 
                             updated or annotated. In practice, an                     
                             OLE2 file should never fall back to XSSF.                 
                             7. Similar patterns:                                      
                                - The `DocumentFactoryHelper` in POI                   
                             properly lets parse exceptions bubble out                 
                             for matched document types. We follow the                 
                             same pattern in `WorkbookFactory`.                        
                                - Other Apache libraries (e.g.,                        
                             XMLBeans) immediately propagate parsing                   
                             exceptions once the correct format is                     
                             detected.                                                 
                             <code_range>poi/src/main/java/org/apache/                 
                             poi/ss/usermodel/WorkbookFactory.java:150                 
                             -220</code_range>                                         
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>                                           
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                                                                                       
                             The projects fuzzing harness ran Jazzer                  
                             against Apache POIs `WorkbookFactory`,                   
                             exercising its format-detection and                       
                             provider-based dispatch logic. An                         
                             attempted refactoring replaced the                        
                             original `create(DirectoryNode, String)`                  
                             and related code with a new private                       
                             helper `wp(FileMagic, ProviderMethod)` to                 
                             centralize magic-based dispatch. After                    
                             applying the patch, the build fails in                    
                             `WorkbookFactory.java` with a flood of                    
                             illegal start of type and ;                          
                             expected errors, all pointing at what                    
                             used to be the Javadoc and the subsequent                 
                             `create(InputStream)` methods. The                       
                             errors indicate that comment markers                      
                             and/or braces were misaligned or removed                  
                             incorrectly, leaving stray `*` characters                 
                             and unclosed Javadoc or method blocks.                    
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Initial Issue                                          
                                - The fuzzer output shows successful                   
                             instrumentation of hundreds of POI                        
                             classes and runs without crashing.                        
                                - This indicates the entry-point                       
                             (`POIHSSFFuzzer`) and harness are working                 
                             and not the immediate cause of the                        
                             compilation failure.                                      
                                                                                       
                             2. Patch Attempt                                          
                                - In `WorkbookFactory.java`, around                    
                             line 148:                                                 
                                   The original public static                         
                             `create(DirectoryNode root, String                        
                             password)` method (plus its Javadoc) was                  
                             removed.                                                  
                                   A new private static method                        
                                    ```java                                            
                                    private static Workbook                            
                             wp(FileMagic magic, ProviderMethod                        
                             method) throws IOException {  }                          
                                    ```                                                
                                    was inserted to select a                           
                             `WorkbookProvider` based on `magic` and                   
                             invoke `method.create(prov)`.                             
                                - No further context was shown, but                    
                             the patch appears to have deleted or                      
                             truncated the leading `/** ... */`                        
                             Javadoc opener for the next                               
                             `create(InputStream inp)` methods.                        
                                                                                       
                             3. Patch Result and Build Log                             
                                - Compilation errors all start at or                   
                             just before line 182 in                                   
                             `WorkbookFactory.java`, where stray `*`                   
                             and Javadoc tags (`@param`, `@return`,                    
                             `@throws`) are now being parsed as code.                  
                                - Errors include illegal start of                     
                             type, `; expected, and identifier                    
                             expected on lines that look like comment                 
                             lines.                                                    
                                - Following the comment errors, the                    
                             signatures for                                            
                                  ```java                                              
                                  public static Workbook                               
                             create(InputStream inp) throws                            
                             IOException, EncryptedDocumentException {                 
                              }                                                       
                                  public static Workbook                               
                             create(InputStream inp, String password)                  
                             throws IOException,                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException {  }                          
                                  ```                                                  
                                  are also flagged as illegal start                   
                             of expression, indicating that the                       
                             parser never saw the end of the previous                  
                             comment or method.                                        
                                                                                       
                             4. Key Observations & Next Steps                          
                                - The Javadoc block preceding                          
                             `create(InputStream)` is malformed or                    
                             missing its opening `/**`.                                
                                - A mismatched closing brace (`}`) or                  
                             misplaced comment delimiter may have left                 
                             the compiler inside a comment or method                   
                             body.                                                     
                                - The patch introduces new code but                    
                             does not show how it adjusts surrounding                  
                             braces or comments, so the region from                    
                             the end of `wp(...)` through the next                     
                             public methods needs careful review.                      
                                - To get a holistic view, review the                   
                             full `WorkbookFactory.java` around:                       
                                   The end of the new `wp(...)`                       
                             method (matching braces)                                  
                                   The Javadoc comment delimiters                     
                             before `create(InputStream)`                             
                                   Any class-level or provider-list                   
                             declarations that the patch referenced                    
                             (`provider`)                                              
                                - Ensuring that all `/** ... */`                       
                             comments are properly opened and closed,                  
                             and that every method block has matching                  
                             `{}` will resolve the syntax errors.

                             ```                                                       
                             140:     * Workbook should be closed                      
                             after use.                                                
                             141:     *                                                
                             142:     * @param root The {@link                         
                             DirectoryNode} to start reading the                       
                             document from                                             
                             143:     * @param password The password                   
                             that should be used or null if no                         
                             password is necessary.                                    
                             144:     *                                                
                             145:     * @return The created Workbook                   
                             146:     *                                                
                             147:     * @throws IOException if an                      
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             148:     * @throws IllegalStateException                  
                             a number of runtime exceptions can be                     
                             thrown, especially if there are problems                  
                             with the                                                  
                             149:     * input format                                   
                             150:     */                                               
                             151:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(final DirectoryNode root, String                   
                             password) throws IOException {                            
                             152:        // Encrypted OOXML files go                   
                             inside OLE2 containers, is this one?                      
                             153:        if                                            
                             (root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(DEFAULT_POI                 
                             FS_ENTRY) ||                                              
                             root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(OOXML_PACKAG                 
                             E)) {                                                     
                             154:            return                                    
                             wp(FileMagic.OOXML, w -> w.create(root,                   
                             password));                                               
                             155:        } else {                                      
                             156:            return wp(FileMagic.OLE2,                 
                             w ->  w.create(root, password));                          
                             157:        }                                             
                             158:    }                                                 
                             159:                                                      
                             160:    /**                                               
                             161:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             162:     *  the given InputStream.                        
                             163:     *                                                
                             164:     * <p>Your input stream MUST                      
                             either support mark/reset, or                             
                             165:     *  be wrapped as a {@link                        
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             166:     *  Note that using an {@link                     
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             167:     *  than using a {@link                           
                             File}.</p>                                                
                             168:     *                                                
                             169:     * <p>Note that in order to                       
                             properly release resources the                            
                             170:     *  Workbook should be closed                     
                             after use. Note also that loading                         
                             171:     *  from an InputStream requires                  
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             172:     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                 
                             #create(File)} where possible.                            
                             173:     *                                                
                             174:     *  @param inp The {@link                         
                             InputStream} to read data from.                           
                             175:     *                                                
                             176:     *  @return The created Workbook                  
                             177:     *                                                
                             178:     *  @throws IOException if an                     
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             179:     *  @throws                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException If the                         
                             Workbook given is password protected                      
                             180:     *  @throws EmptyFileException If                 
                             the given data is empty                                   
                             181:     *  @throws IllegalStateException                 
                             a number of other runtime exceptions can                  
                             be thrown, especially if there are                        
                             problems with the                                         
                             182:     *  input format                                  
                             183:     */                                               
                             184:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(InputStream inp) throws                            
                             IOException, EncryptedDocumentException {                 
                             185:        return create(inp, null);                     
                             186:    }                                                 
                             187:                                                      
                             188:    /**                                               
                             189:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             190:     *  the given InputStream, which                  
                             may be password protected.                                
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>                                                   
                             <code>                                                    
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/ss/userm                 
                             odel/WorkbookFactory.java:184-240                         
                             ```                                                       
                             184:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(InputStream inp) throws                            
                             IOException, EncryptedDocumentException {                 
                             185:        return create(inp, null);                     
                             186:    }                                                 
                             187:                                                      
                             188:    /**                                               
                             189:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             190:     *  the given InputStream, which                  
                             may be password protected.                                
                             191:     *                                                
                             192:     * <p>Your input stream MUST                      
                             either support mark/reset, or                             
                             193:     *  be wrapped as a {@link                        
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             194:     *  Note that using an {@link                     
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             195:     *  than using a {@link                           
                             File}.</p>                                                
                             196:     *                                                
                             197:     * <p>Note that in order to                       
                             properly release resources the                            
                             198:     *  Workbook should be closed                     
                             after use. Note also that loading                         
                             199:     *  from an InputStream requires                  
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             200:     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                 
                             #create(File)} where possible.</p>                        
                             201:     *                                                
                             202:     *  @param inp The {@link                         
                             InputStream} to read data from.                           
                             203:     *  @param password The password                  
                             that should be used or null if no                         
                             password is necessary.                                    
                             204:     *                                                
                             205:     *  @return The created Workbook                  
                             206:     *                                                
                             207:     *  @throws IOException if an                     
                             error occurs while reading the data                       
                             208:     *  @throws                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException If the wrong                   
                             password is given for a protected file                    
                             209:     *  @throws EmptyFileException If                 
                             the given data is empty                                   
                             210:     *  @throws IllegalStateException                 
                             a number of other runtime exceptions can                  
                             be thrown, especially if there are                        
                             problems with the                                         
                             211:     *  input format                                  
                             212:     */                                               
                             213:    public static Workbook                            
                             create(InputStream inp, String password)                  
                             throws IOException,                                       
                             EncryptedDocumentException {                              
                             214:        InputStream is =                              
                             FileMagic.prepareToCheckMagic(inp);                       
                             215:        byte[] emptyFileCheck = new                   
                             byte[1];                                                  
                             216:                                                      
                             is.mark(emptyFileCheck.length);                           
                             217:        if (is.read(emptyFileCheck) <                 
                             emptyFileCheck.length) {                                  
                             218:            throw new                                 
                             EmptyFileException();                                     
                             219:        }                                             
                             220:        is.reset();                                   
                             221:                                                      
                             222:        final FileMagic fm =                          
                             FileMagic.valueOf(is);                                    
                             223:        if (FileMagic.OOXML == fm) {                  
                             224:            return wp(fm, w ->                        
                             w.create(is));                                            
                             225:        }                                             
                             226:                                                      
                             227:        if (FileMagic.OLE2 != fm) {                   
                             228:            throw new                                 
                             IOException("Can't open workbook -                        
                             unsupported file type: "+fm);                             
                             229:        }                                             
                             230:                                                      
                             231:        POIFSFileSystem poifs = new                   
                             POIFSFileSystem(is);                                      
                             232:        DirectoryNode root =                          
                             poifs.getRoot();                                          
                             233:        boolean isOOXML =                             
                             root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(DEFAULT_POIF                 
                             S_ENTRY) ||                                               
                             root.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(OOXML_PACKAG                 
                             E);                                                       
                             234:                                                      
                             235:        return wp(isOOXML ?                           
                             FileMagic.OOXML : fm, w -> w.create(root,                 
                             password));                                               
                             236:    }                                                 
                             237:                                                      
                             238:    /**                                               
                             239:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             240:     *  the given File, which must                    
                             exist and be readable.                                    
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>

                             17:package org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel;                   
                             18:                                                       
                             19:import static                                          
                             org.apache.poi.extractor.ExtractorFactory                 
                             .OOXML_PACKAGE;                                           
                             20:import static                                          
                             org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.Decryptor.DEFA                 
                             ULT_POIFS_ENTRY;                                          
                             21:                                                       
                             22:import java.io.BufferedInputStream;                    
                             23:import java.io.File;                                   
                             24:import java.io.FileNotFoundException;                  
                             25:import java.io.IOException;                            
                             26:import java.io.InputStream;                            
                             27:import java.util.ArrayList;                            
                             28:import java.util.List;                                 
                             29:import java.util.ServiceLoader;                        
                             30:                                                       
                             31:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.EmptyFileException;                        
                             32:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.EncryptedDocumentException                 
                             ;                                                         
                             33:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.hssf.usermodel.HSSFWorkboo                 
                             k;                                                        
                             34:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.Directory                 
                             Node;                                                     
                             35:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.FileMagic                 
                             ;                                                         
                             36:import                                                 
                             org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.POIFSFile                 
                             System;                                                   
                             37:                                                       
                             38:/**                                                    
                             39: * Factory for creating the                            
                             appropriate kind of Workbook                              
                             40: *  (be it {@link HSSFWorkbook} or                     
                             XSSFWorkbook),                                            
                             41: *  by auto-detecting from the                         
                             supplied input.                                           
                             42: */                                                    
                             43:public final class WorkbookFactory {                   
                             44:                                                       
                             45:    private static class Singleton {                   
                             46:        private static final                           
                             WorkbookFactory INSTANCE = new                            
                             WorkbookFactory();                                        
                             47:    }                                                  
                             48:                                                       
                             49:    private interface ProviderMethod {                 
                             50:        Workbook                                       
                             create(WorkbookProvider prov) throws                      
                             IOException;                                              
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>                                                   
                             <code>                                                    
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/ss/userm                 
                             odel/WorkbookFactory.java:320-344                         
                             ```                                                       
                             320:            throw new                                 
                             IOException("Can't open workbook -                        
                             unsupported file type: "+fm);                             
                             321:        }                                             
                             322:    }                                                 
                             323:                                                      
                             324:                                                      
                             325:    private static Workbook                           
                             wp(FileMagic fm, ProviderMethod fun)                      
                             throws IOException {                                      
                             326:                                                      
                             327:        for (WorkbookProvider prov :                  
                             Singleton.INSTANCE.provider) {                            
                             328:            if (prov.accepts(fm)) {                   
                             329:                return                                
                             fun.create(prov);                                         
                             330:            }                                         
                             331:        }                                             
                             332:        throw new IOException("Your                   
                             InputStream was neither an OLE2 stream,                   
                             nor an OOXML stream " +                                   
                             333:            "or you haven't provide

                             161:     * Creates the appropriate                        
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                             162:     *  the given InputStream.                        
                             163:     *

                             either support mark/reset, or                             
                             165:     *  be wrapped as a {@link                        
                             BufferedInputStream}!                                     
                             166:     *  Note that using an {@link                     
                             InputStream} has a higher memory                          
                             footprint                                                 
                             167:     *  than using a {@link                           
                             File}.</p>                                                
                             168:     *                                                
                             169:     * <p>Note that in order to                       
                             properly release resources the                            
                             170:     *  Workbook should be closed                     
                             after use. Note also that loading                         
                             171:     *  from an InputStream requires                  
                             more memory than loading                                  
                             172:     *  from a File, so prefer {@link                 
                             #create(File)} where possible.                            
                             173:     *                                                
                             174:     *  @param inp The {@link                         
                             InputStream} to read data from.

                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Review and restore the Javadoc/brace                   
                             boundary around the new private `wp(...)`                 
                             helper so that it does not bleed into                   
                             the publicAPI Javadoc for the                            
                             `create(InputStream)` overloads.  In                     
                             practice this means:                                      
                                                                                       
                                a. Immediately after the closing `}`                   
                             of the newly added                                        
                                   `private static Workbook                            
                             wp(FileMagic magic, ProviderMethod                        
                             method) throws IOException {  }`                         
                                   remove any stray lines beginning                    
                             with `*` that were inadvertently left in                  
                             the patch.                                                
                                                                                       
                                b. Directly below that `}` insert                      
                             exactly one blank line, then ensure the                   
                             Javadoc for the next public method begins                 
                             with `/**`.  For example:                                 
                                   ```                                                 
                                   }  // end of private wp helper                      
                                                                                       
                                   /**                                                 
                                    * Creates the appropriate                          
                             HSSFWorkbook / XSSFWorkbook from                          
                                    * the given InputStream.                           
                                    *                                                 
                                    */                                                 
                                   public static Workbook                              
                             create(InputStream inp) throws                            
                             IOException, EncryptedDocumentException {                 
                                       return create(inp, null);                       
                                   }                                                   
                                   ```                                                 
                                c. Verify the matching `*/` appears                    
                             immediately before the `public static                     
                             Workbook create(InputStream, String)`                     
                             signature, and that there are no missing                  
                             or extra braces between methods.                          
                                                                                       
                             2. Ensure that every opening `/**` in the                 
                             file is closed by a corresponding `*/`                    
                             before the next method or class                           
                             declaration.  In particular:                              
                                - The Javadoc for the removed (or                      
                             refactored) `create(DirectoryNode,                        
                             String)` must still terminate cleanly                     
                             before the `private wp` insertion.                        
                                - The two Javadoc blocks for                           
                             `create(InputStream)` and                                 
                             `create(InputStream, String)` must each                   
                             be correctly delimited.                                   
                                                                                       
                             3. If the new `wp` helper is currently                    
                             sandwiched between two Javadoc blocks,                    
                             consider moving it to the end of the                      
                             class (immediately before `addProvider` /                 
                             `removeProvider`) so that all publicAPI                  
                             overloads remain together, reducing the                   
                             risk of comment misalignment.                            
                                                                                       
                             4. After reorganizing:                                    
                                - Run `mvn compile` (or `gradle                        
                             compileJava`) to confirm no illegal                      
                             start of type or `';' expected` errors                   
                             remain.                                                   
                                - Review the brace nesting (e.g., via                  
                             your IDEs codefolding or a linter) to                   
                             ensure each method and class closes                       
                             exactly once.                                             
                                - Confirm that all public API                          
                             signatures and Javadocs are exactly as                    
                             they were before the patch (aside from                    
                             the intended refactoring).                                
                                                                                       
                             Justification:                                            
                             - The compilation failures all stem from                  
                             a malformed Javadoc/missingbrace                         
                             boundary that causes the compiler to                      
                             treat leading `*` tokens as code. By                      
                             restoring the `/**  */` wrappers and                     
                             ensuring the `wp` method is fully closed                  
                             before the next comment, we eliminate the                 
                             syntax errors.                                            
                             - This strategy preserves all existing                    
                             publicAPI methods and their                              
                             documentation (other than the intended                    
                             refactoring), avoids touching harness or                  
                             fuzzing code, and keeps the new `wp`                      
                             helper logically in place.                                
                             - Moving the helper to the end of the                     
                             class further isolates it from publicAPI                 
                             comment blocks, reducing the chance of                    
                             future Javadoc misalignment.                              
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>
